HEADWORD: Nimiety
<hw>Ni*mi"e*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>nimietas</ets>, fr. <ets>nimius</ets>, a., <ets>nimis</ets>, adv.,
too much.]</ety> <def>State of being in excess.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There is a <qex>nimiety</qex>, a too-muchness, in all Germans.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

